```
From: Jared Isaacman
Sent: Monday, June 24, 2019 3:47 PM
To:
Cc:
Subject:

All,
Effective immediately, I am resigning from my position as Chief Executive Officer. It has
become clear to me in recent weeks that the path the company is on is not consistent
with my vision and goals for the business nor the commitments I made for ongoing
support, strategy, stability and growth
Shift4 Payments, nor the commitments I made to many employees throughout the organization.
Specifically, the decision to terminate some of the companies
most valuable sales and marketing employees, without consulting leadership, against the
advice of most of our senior executives, is completely unacceptable.
Further, the decision to process the volume of an individual, and the related economics to
be recognized by another entity, that has been an illegal enterprise engaging in fraudulent
activity for many-years, is contrary to all of the regulatory, compliance and ethical controls
I have put into place at Shift4 Payments. This is not an organization I wish to be a
part of any longer.
Thank you,
Jared
```
